Our culture has become angrier; ruder; cruder; louder; less tolerant and more violent. People are more afraid; less hopeful; more tribal. Is it fair to place all this at the feet of the President? Of course not; nothing is that simple.

When a President routinely condemns; ridicules and denigrates others; uses language that is offensive and racist; foments resentment; fear and grievance for political purposes; then there are real consequences.

As the President; Mr. Trump sets the tone. There are other politicians whose tone and language are also destructive. But there is only one President. And so we must hold every President to a higher standard. Such is the price and the responsibility of the Office.

Behavior; language; and tone are all about “how things get done”. They define character. Character is revealed over time in the pattern of behavior; language and tone. And character is destiny; for a person and for a nation.
Over decades I have developed leaders of all kinds in all kinds of places through both my business and charitable work; so I know how things get done is always as important as what gets done.
In the midst of all these important conversations; let us pause and reflect on the one thing we all know to be true: character counts and tone is set at the top.
